The paper discusses the combination of Interactive Evolutionary Computation (IEC) with an eye-tracker for visual optimization, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The use of data mining techniques on gaze information also suggests a focus on Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of an eye-tracker for visual optimization, which is a common tool in Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the results of experiments conducted on human individuals, which suggests a focus on Information Retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of analyzing and interpreting the data collected.
